OL,3,CJohn Torode says allegation of using
OL,4,Cracist language upheld in MasterChef
OL,5,Creview
OL,7,FMasterChef presenter John Torode has
OL,8,Fconfirmed he is the subject of an
OL,9,Fallegation of using racist language
OL,10,Fthat was upheld as part of a review
OL,11,Finto the behaviour of his co-presenter
OL,12,FGregg Wallace.
OL,14,FThe report, commissioned by MasterChef
OL,15,Fproduction company Banijay and led by
OL,16,Flaw firm Lewis Silkin, found 45 out of
OL,17,F83 allegations against Wallace were
OL,18,Fsubstantiated, alongside two
OL,19,Fstandalone allegations made against
OL,20,Fother people, including one for using
OL,21,Fracist language.
